        <headline>Flood Advisory issued August 23 at 10:12AM EDT until August 23 at 12:15PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast South Carolina, including the
following counties, Beaufort, Charleston and Colleton.

* WHEN...Until 1215 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Water over roadways. Overflowing poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 1010 AM EDT, Doppler radar indicated a band of moderate to
locally heavy rainfall extending from Edisto Island to
Hunting Island. This band will drift to the southwest. A
quick inch of rain is possible near high tide. The elevated
tide will likely prevent adequate draining in some areas,
resulting in minor flooding of low-lying and poor drainage
areas.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Hilton Head Island, Edisto Beach, Fripp Island, Parris
Island, Hilton Head Airport, Coffin Point, Hunting Island,
Harbor Island, Eddings Point and Penn Center.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
